# Rust build output (massive; regenerated on `cargo build`).
/target/

# Local runtime/tooling output.
/.saydeploy/
/.vscode/
/.idea/

# Per-run files written next to the exe.
quickdictate.log
quickdictate-panic.log
quickdictate-dev-port.txt
quickdictate-update.txt
key-health.json

# Connections settings-sync: DPAPI-sealed refresh token (machine+user bound).
# Never plaintext, never committed.
quickdictate-connections.dat

# Self-update leftovers (old/new exe during the in-place swap).
*.old
*.new

# The user's REAL config may contain their own API keys — never commit it.
# Ship settings.example.json (empty keys) as the template instead.
settings.json

# Secrets / env.
# `*.env` is broad on purpose: any local env file holding keys (my.keys.env,
# *.local.env, etc.) is ignored by default so no credential can slip in.
.env
*.env
*.pem
*.key

# Packaged artifacts / loose binaries.
*.zip
*.7z
*.rar
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.exe

# Generated test audio (recreate with scripts/gen_test_audio.ps1). The live
# provider tests are #[ignore] + need real keys, so these aren't needed in CI.
tests/fixtures/*.wav

# Headless UI screenshots (scripts/ui_shot.ps1) — dev-only artifacts.
ui-shot*.png
ui-*.png

# Backups / editor cruft.
**/*.rs.bk
**/*.rs.b4
*~

# Local investigation / handoff notes (not for the repo).
*_HANDOFF.md
SCRIBE_HALLUCINATION_HANDOFF.md
